children.name: Theemo allows to have transforms on Local Variables. To make them work with the mechanics available to a Figma Plugin is a little tricky. Demonstrating this with a color palette from 100-900. The center value (500) is the actual value and the other values are transformed with lightness in steps of 10. Create the Variables, in this case a color palette from 100 to 900 Give 500 a value of your choice Assign all the others 100-400 and 600-900 to reference the 500 value Create styles to represent the variables Assign the styles to their respective variable Open Theemo plugin, and find one style, let’s say brand/400 Give it a lightness of -10 The reference association will disappear in the Local Variables window, that is by design. The reference is taken over by theemo. You can find it in the comment to the .theemo/config grid style. By using styles, Theemo can intercept this and apply transforms. Now go and change the local variable of brand/500 to something else. When Theemo is opened, all other style values will follow.
children.characters:
Theemo allows to have transforms on Local Variables. To make them work with the mechanics available to a 
Figma Plugin is a little tricky.

Demonstrating this with a color palette from 100-900. The center value (500) is the actual value and the other
values are transformed with lightness in steps of 10.

Create the Variables, in this case a color palette from 100 to 900
Give 500 a value of your choice
Assign all the others 100-400 and 600-900 to reference the 500 value
Create styles to represent the variables
Assign the styles to their respective variable
Open Theemo plugin, and find one style, let’s say brand/400
Give it a lightness of -10

The reference association will disappear in the Local Variables window, that is by design. The reference is taken
over by theemo. You can find it in the comment to the .theemo/config grid style.

By using styles, Theemo can intercept this and apply transforms. Now go and change the local variable of brand/500
to something else. When Theemo is opened, all other style values will follow.
